<p>What I'm trying to do here is to filter all markers on the map to get the near ones, then only show markers that are at a defined range of current position, markers are filtered and created, but the infowindows are not triggered when clicked, I think you need to set a variable for each marker, but I don't know how to implement this on my current code. All markers are received through a JSON.</p>  <p>Here is my code</p>  <pre><code>if (navigator.geolocation) {             navigator.geolocation.getCurrentPosition(showPosition);         } function showPosition(position) {     checkMap = setInterval("bbCenter("+ position.coords.latitude + "," + position.coords.longitude + ")",500); }     var newCenter = new google.maps.LatLng(latitude, longitude);//             nameofmap.setCenter(newCenter);             clearInterval(checkMap);             var marker, distcenter;             var dist = 6;//Distance in kilometers for filtering markers             for (i = 0; i&lt; jsonMarkers.length; i++){                 marker = new google.maps.LatLng(jsonMarkers[i].lat,jsonMarkers[i].lng);                 distcenter = (google.maps.geometry.spherical.computeDistanceBetween(marker,newCenter)/1000).toFixed(2);//Gets distance in kilometers of marker to current position                 if (distcenter&lt;dist){//Add filtered markers                    agregarMarcador(marker,jsonMarkers[i].title,jsonMarkers[i].icon,jsonMarkers[i].description);                 }             }             function agregarMarcador (ubicacion, titulo, icono, descripcion){                 marcador = new google.maps.Marker({                     title: titulo,                     position: ubicacion,                     map: nameofmap,                 });                 ventana = new google.maps.InfoWindow({                     position: ubicacion,                     maxWidth: 200,                     content: '&lt;h4&gt;'+titulo+'&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;div class="mark-descr"&gt;'+descripcion+'&lt;/div&gt;',                 });                 google.maps.event.addListener(marcador, 'click', function() {                     infowindow.open(nameofmap, ventana);                 });             } </code></pre>  <p>It is possible to generate variable names on a for? I don't think it would be a good approach, but I haven't found the correct way for creating the arrays for the infowindows. Is there any other way of linking them to the click event?</p>